# Verify Rust work before finishing

Before ending a task that changes Rust code, run verification commands from the repo root:

- First resolve Cargo in non-interactive shells:
  - Prefer `cargo` from `PATH`.
  - If missing, use `"$HOME/.cargo/bin/cargo"` (or run with `PATH="$HOME/.cargo/bin:$PATH"`).
- Build check: `cargo check` (or `cargo check -p <crate>` when edits are confined to one workspace member). If `cargo` is not on `PATH`, run `"$HOME/.cargo/bin/cargo" check ...`.
- Tests: `cargo test` (or `cargo test -p <crate>` when edits are confined to one workspace member). If `cargo` is not on `PATH`, run `"$HOME/.cargo/bin/cargo" test ...`.
- If `CEF_PATH` points at a missing tree and the build fails in `cef-dll-sys`, use `env -u CEF_PATH` with the same command, or match the project `Makefile` / docs.

Do not only suggest commands; run them when shell access is available and fix reported issues before handing off.
